    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/38.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1615.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram, No. 251, of December 23, 4 p.m., stating that the time for
                    revalidating mining titles has been extended to March 31, 1915, by a decree of
                    the administration at Mexico City, but that the regulations and penalties
                    previously imposed have not been revoked, and that you have taken up the matter
                    with Señor Gutierrez, with a view to their modification or abolition.</p>
                <p>The Department cordially approves your course in taking up the matter with Señor
                    Gutierrez, and thanks you for your action in the premises.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
